SUMMARY:When Everyone Swims w/filmmaker | New Americas Cinema
DESCRIPTION:When Everyone Swims is a compilation of inspirational and ins
 ightful stories about how everyone deserves access to pools and safe plac
 es to swim. Through powerful\, personal narratives\, the film celebrates 
 resilience and highlights how water literacy can help individuals from al
 l backgrounds build healthy\, life-affirming relationships with the water
 . [90 min\; documentary\; English]A Q&amp\;A with director Jerald Harknes
 s\, Olympic medalist Lilly King\, and production consultant Dr. Tiffany M
 onique Quash\, moderated by Bill Ramos of the School of Public Health\, w
 ill follow the screening.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p><i>When Everyone Swims</i> is a compilati
 on of inspirational and insightful stories about how everyone deserves ac
 cess to pools and safe places to swim. Through powerful\, personal narrat
 ives\, the film celebrates resilience and highlights how water literacy c
 an help individuals from all backgrounds build healthy\, life-affirming r
 elationships with the water. [90 min\; documentary\; English]</p><p><i><s
 trong>A Q&amp\;A with director Jerald Harkness\, Olympic medalist Lilly K
 ing\, and production consultant Dr. Tiffany Monique Quash\, moderated by 
 Bill Ramos of the School of Public Health\, will follow the screening.</s
 trong></i></p>
